<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: TOPIC: PvP SERVER WITH NO LVL LIMIT -OPINIONS?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Mizari">Mizari</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:03 p.m. 10/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: TOPIC: PvP SERVER WITH NO LVL LIMIT -OPINIONS?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=537" TARGET=_self>TOPIC: PvP SERVER WITH NO LVL LIMIT -OPINIONS?</A> (Geiger)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>In my opinion a server with no level *constraints* would not be playable within EQ. In order to advance in the game it takes months to build a decent character... and there is no way to do so without going out into the cold harsh world and grunting for it. It would be in the best interest of all the bigger players to do their best to keep the smaller ones small. There may be little loot in it for them and no challenge... but by killing off the weak whenever possible there's less competition they'd have to worry about. This would translate directly into guilds where larger guilds would still be able to pick off and destroy the larger individual players, thereby completely dominating the game.

<P>Death here has serious bite, constant dying will not annoy but rather destroy a character. Due to the time involved in building a character it would soon become a case of the extremely powerful and the extremely weak with no room for movement from the lower ranks without the explicit support of one of the powerful guilds. Level advantages already create a gulf between players... allowing them to be exploited would only make it worse.
<P>Is the +/-4 best way to prevent this? No probably not, I think RealmWeaver among others has suggested some excellent alternatives which should be seriously looked at and considered. With some strong game based incentives away from rabid dog PvP mobs and more towards playing within the factions and/or principles of a class/race I think the hard coded limits could be done away with successfully. In the meantime however my view is it's a necessary evil until a better solution can be delivered.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
